                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18009</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eagle Pass</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegram just received from General Obregon at Chihuahua, when translated,
                    states: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Please inform your Government I will confer with General Scott at Juarez.
                            Am leaving for there to-morrow.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>General Scott advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
